ethod, you will notice, is static. It belongs to the class it's declared in, rather than to any instance objects. This means, outside of itself, the main method knows only about the class that it's in, and any other static methods or objects in that class. Things that are not static belong to the actual objects created from the class -- and the main method will know nothing about these actual objects, unless they are created inside of the main method itself.
